{"content":{"body":"Native events are synchronous in the sense that if multiple event dispatches or callbacks or promise resolutions occur in the same task, each can observe each other's side effects in order. It is roughly \"call all the event listeners and then perform a mictotask checkpoint\". ","m.relates_to":{"event_id":"$J5oBFMPGzUjAGpP1jhoTbulgJNktJ1RZKOpr_NMEi78","is_falling_back":true,"m.in_reply_to":{"event_id":"$B7z3Y3n5mIclw9HtD1XNb-QYhW_YLj_O-lel8SYqnvI"},"rel_type":"m.thread"},"msgtype":"m.text"},"ts":1774856233207,"senderName":"Noam Rosenthal","senderId":"@noamr:matrix.org","id":"$p9Yh1UbtovdcLL1hctpedz0E4i3gEjMtyQbgqhACKSc"},
